"Chicken Tikka Kabab on Tawa" is a delicious  dish that features marinated chicken pieces cooked on a tawa. The chicken is typically marinated in a blend of yogurt, spices (like garam masala, cumin, coriander, turmeric, and red chili powder), and herbs. It is then skewered or placed directly on the tawa to cook, resulting in juicy, flavorful, and slightly charred pieces of chicken.
The dish is often served with naan, paratha, or rice and accompanied by condiments like green chutney and onions. It's a popular snack or appetizer, especially at parties or in street food settings. The tawa gives the chicken a distinctive smoky and grilled flavor, making it a savory and aromatic dish loved by many.

Nutritious Kanji | Amala | Turmeric | Fermented Indian Drink
youtube_description:
Amla Ginger Turmeric Kanji


This drink is incredibly refreshing with its spicy and bold flavors. Considering the health benefits, especially during winter when cold and cough are common, this fermented drink is a fantastic option. Itâ€™s nutritious, great for gut health, and perfect to have mid-morning or mid-evening.

Hope you try this drink !


3 Amla
2 Ginger roots
2 Turmeric roots
3 Green chilies
Black salt: 1 tbsp
White mustard seeds: 1Â½ tbsp (coarsely ground)
Water: 1Â½ liters

All right, to make Amla, Ginger, Turmeric Kanji, start by cleaning the amla. I have cleaned the amla, ginger, turmeric, and chillies in salt water. Then, you can peel the skin. I peeled the skin because it was still dirty, but you can keep the skin on if you have organic or homegrown produce. After cleaning and peeling, chop all the ingredients and add them to a jar along with black salt and coarsely crushed white mustard seeds. Pour one and a half liters of water into the jar and mix well. Cover the jar with a cloth, ensuring it is not airtight, as the mixture needs air for fermentation.

Place the jar in sunlight from 9 AM to 5 PM for 2 to 5 days, depending on the weather. If the weather is hot, fermentation will take about 2 days, while colder weather may require 4 to 5 days. Mix it everyday. Bring the jar indoors at night and return it to sunlight the following morning. Once fermented, you will notice tiny bubbles forming on the surface, and the liquid will appear slightly cloudy. Strain the kanji and store it in the refrigerator. It can be kept for 10 to 15 days and enjoyed as a refreshing drink whenever you need.

Ingredients for Tikki:

Method:
 1. Add sprouted moong, carrot, green chillies, ginger, coriander leaves, and boiled potato to a blender. Pulse â€” donâ€™t make it into a paste.

youtube_title: Ragi Cucumber Uttappa | Ragi Dosa | Gut-friendly | Iron - Calcium Rich
youtube_description:
Ragi Cucumber Uttappa

I developed this soft, fermented and nutrient-dense breakfast. ðŸŒ¿
Prepared with ragi, brown rice, urad dal and cooling veggies.
Itâ€™s light on the stomach, gut-friendly and truly wholesome.


Ingredients

For the batter:
 â€¢ 1 cup whole ragi (finger millet)
 â€¢ 1 cup brown rice
 â€¢ 1 cup urad dal
 â€¢ 2 tsp fenugreek seeds
 â€¢ Water (for soaking & grinding)

For mixing after fermentation:
 â€¢ 1 cup grated cucumber
 â€¢ Â¼ cup grated carrot (optional)
 â€¢ Â¼ cup finely chopped onion
 â€¢ 1â€“2 green chillies, 1 inch ginger finely chopped
 â€¢ 2 tbsp coriander leaves, chopped
 â€¢ 1 tsp cumin powder
 â€¢ 1 tsp hing (asafoetida)
 â€¢ Salt to taste

For cooking:
 â€¢ Oil or ghee as needed
 â€¢ Hot tawa/pan

Method

 â€¢ Rinse ragi, brown rice, urad dal, and fenugreek seeds.
 â€¢ Soak everything together for 6â€“7 hours.
 â€¢ Drain the water.
 â€¢ Blend using fresh water to make a smooth, medium-thick batter.
 â€¢ Transfer to a bowl.
 â€¢ Cover and allow the batter to ferment for 8â€“9 hours or overnight.
 â€¢ The batter should rise, look airy, and feel light.
Into the fermented batter, mix:
 â€¢ Grated cucumber
 â€¢ Carrot, onion
 â€¢ Green chilli, ginger, coriander
 â€¢ Cumin powder, hing, and salt
Mix gently without deflating the batter too much.

Ulavakattu is a traditional comfort dish from the Uttara Andhra region made with horse gram and tangy tamarind flavour
It is thick rich and full of earthy taste which makes it perfect to mix with hot steamed rice

The real magic happens when you pair it with a simple village style omelette
The omelette is made with finely chopped onions green chillies fresh coriander salt chilli powder and turmeric mixed with eggs

When cooked on a hot pan until golden and soft it becomes the best side dish for Ulavakattu rice
The crunch of onions the spicy kick of chillies and the freshness of coriander make every bite feel special

This combination is simple homely and loved in many Andhra households
